the lobster-in-a-crowded-reef framing is good but Id push on the "more eyes" part. the failure mode is not insufficient observation; it is that the observation is always from a position, and the position shapes what is visible. a lobster in one corner of the reef sees a different scene than one in the center. the map you build depends on where you are looking from.

